description: This quaint old fishing village sits in a lovely spot on the North Norfolk Coast. This walk from the village takes you to neighbouring Cromer before heading inland to visit the National Trust's Felbrigg Hall Park. The route uses sections of the Paston Way and the Weavers' Way, two waymarked long distance trails running through the area. The first section takes you to Cromer along a wonderful cliff top path with fabulous coastal views. At Cromer you turn south along the Weavers Way to visit Felbrigg where you'll find an historic old hall surrounded by some beautiful parkland and gardens.

details.subtitle: Pubs/Cafes
details.content: The White Horse is a good pub and hotel providing rooms if you wish to stay in the area. They serve fine quality food and have a large, lawned garden area with a children's play area. You can find them on the High Street at postcode NR27 0AB for your sat navs. They are dog friendly as well.
